replies.body:
As:

Most: {{champion:69}} {{champion:28}} {{champion:268}} 

I love some late game ap hypercarry, and cassio and azir also provide a challenge to use, while being very rewarding if you play them well. And about eve, I just love all her theme, the stealthy femme fatale. 

Least: {{champion:25}} 

Morgana is very boring to me, mainly because she has long cd and is very simple to use.

Against:

Most: {{champion:4}} {{champion:6}} 

TF is a nice opponent who can put a lot of pressure in the side lanes with his ult, nevertheless, he is not that oppresive. You gotta play careful against Urgot, he has strengths but clear weaknesses aswell, I think they are both very balanced.

Least: {{champion:238}} 

Let's face it, he is just not fun to play against. He has amazing wave clear/splitpushing, he has burst, poke, he is energy based, he can sustain well once he gets a cutlass. He has mobility, counterplay pontential, dive potential, etc. If you are one of those hypercarries you are not going to have a pretty time against Zed.
